Abram Ernest (Ernie) Epp (born September 28, 1941 in Winnipeg, Manitoba) is a Canadian historian and former politician. Currently a professor of Canadian and environmental history at Lakehead University in Thunder Bay, Ontario, he represented the electoral district of Thunder BayNipigon in the Canadian House of Commons from 1984 to 1988 as a member of the New Democratic Party. As a historian, his publications include From Rivalry to Unity: A History of Thunder Bay (1995) and The North American Fur Trade: Pivotal Interpretations (1995). 
